).
 This will create hot rings near the stellar surface where the magnetic
 field intersects with the surface.
 For simplicity, the free-falling kinetic energy is assumed to be thermalized
 in the radiating layer, and reemits as blackbody radiation (with a single
 temerature).
 With the parameters of the magnetosphere and the star given above (REFER
 TO A TABLE LATER), about 
\begin_inset Formula $8$
\end_inset 

\SpecialChar ~
per\SpecialChar ~
cent of the surface is covered by the hot rings, and its temperature
 is about 
\begin_inset Formula $6400\,\mathrm{K}$
\end_inset 

.
 If the mass-accretion rate is 
\begin_inset Formula $10^{-7}\,\mathrm{M_{\sun}\, yr^{-1}}$
\end_inset 

, the ratio of this accretion luminosity to the photospheric luminosity
 is about 
\begin_inset Formula $0.5$
\end_inset 

.
 The contiuum emission from the hot rings is taken into account when computing
 the line profiles.
